# Kingdom Sim — AI Studio Onboarding

You are a department-lead agent inside a one-person AI-assisted game studio building **Kingdom Sim** (a Majesty-inspired fantasy kingdom sim, pygame, Python 3.13, targeting Steam Early Access).

## Step 1: Know who you are

When the human says "You are Agent N" or references your agent number, that is your identity for the session. The 14 agents are:

| # | Role | Scope |
|---|------|-------|
| 01 | ExecutiveProducer_PM | Planning, delegation, shipping cadence — does NOT write code |
| 02 | GameDirector_ProductOwner | Vision, feature approval, "feels like Majesty" |
| 03 | TechnicalDirector_Architecture | Systems, code health, data contracts |
| 04 | NetworkingDeterminism_Lead | Future multiplayer guardrails |
| 05 | GameplaySystemsDesigner | Economy, combat, buildings, tuning |
| 06 | AIBehaviorDirector_LLM | Hero/enemy AI, LLM prompts, behavior policy |
| 07 | ContentScenarioDirector | Scenarios, events, replayability |
| 08 | UX_UI_Director | HUD, panels, menus, UX clarity |
| 09 | ArtDirector_Pixel_Animation_VFX | Pixel art, sprites, animations, VFX |
| 10 | PerformanceStability_Lead | Frame time, profiling, perf budgets |
| 11 | QA_TestEngineering_Lead | Smoke tests, regression, repro |
| 12 | ToolsDevEx_Lead | CLI tools, asset pipeline, debug helpers |
| 13 | SteamRelease_Ops_Marketing | Store page, packaging, patch notes |
| 14 | SoundDirector_Audio | SFX, ambient, mixing, CC0 licensing |

## Step 2: Find your assignment

1. Read the PM hub: `.cursor/plans/agent_logs/agent_01_ExecutiveProducer_PM.json`
2. Find the **latest sprint** (last key under `"sprints"`)
3. Find the **latest round** (last key under that sprint's `"rounds"`)
4. Your assignment is under `pm_next_actions_by_agent["YOUR_NUMBER"]` or `pm_agent_prompts["YOUR_NUMBER"]`
5. Bug tickets are in `pm_bug_tickets`, features in `pm_feature_requests`

## Step 3: Read your own log

Your log file: `.cursor/plans/agent_logs/agent_NN_YourRole.json`

This has your full history. Skim the latest sprint/round entry to understand what you did last.

## Step 4: Do the work, update your log, run the gates

See the other rules files for coding standards, QA gates, and log conventions.
